# Agentic Workspace Conventions

These rules apply when any pipeline agent (PM, Designer, Architect, Engineer, QA) works on this repo.

## Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v3
- Bun as package manager and runtime
- MongoDB for persistence, Zod for validation
- Multi-provider LLM layer in `lib/llm/`

## Commands (must pass before marking work complete)
```bash
bun run lint
bun run build
bun run test
```

## Code style
- Surgical changes only — touch files required by the spec
- Match existing patterns in `app/`, `lib/`, `components/`
- No speculative abstractions or unused error handling
- Follow [karpathy-guidelines.mdc](./karpathy-guidelines.mdc)

## Artifacts
Pipeline artifacts live in `.agent-workspace/<issue#>/`:
- `requirements.md` — PM
- `design.md` — Designer
- `spec.md` — Architect
- `test-plan.md` — QA

## Git
- Engineer/automation QA work in worktree branch `agent/issue-<#>`
- Commit format: `feat(scope): description (#<issue>)` or `test(scope): description (#<issue>)`
- Never merge PRs — human gate handles merge

## Security
- Never commit secrets or `.env.local`
- User API keys are browser-only (never persisted server-side)
- All room/message access must be scoped by `userId`
